				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				 Ahhhh, I think all those who speak against twinking and twinks are basically jealous, though certainly exceptions can exist. And same goes for camping items by high levelled characters. If they could, most people would be twinked and would try to get good items on their own. I have a characters stationed in Faydark for the purposes of trading... Thanks to her my main character is decently equipped and I have two horrible pking low level twinks (I play on Tallon Zek). Nothing is as pleasant as wielding a Wurmslayer and wearing Sentry and Sebilite Scale at level 20, except perhaps wielding Velium Brawl Stick and wearing Crystal Chitin... My main character is level 45, totally unable to camp most of the stuff my twinks wear, but simply being able to trade well allowed me to gather good equipment. Hmmm, I suppose my main is a twink, too, then, since my trading character gave her most of her equipment. Trivial Loot Code is most certainly an abomination - people should be rewarded for growing stronger, not punished for it. But whether is' there or not, my few camping experience were traumatic and annoying (spending three days in Crystal Caverns, trying to get a Ry'Gorr Oracle Cloak while I could've made the money for it in a day). Furthermore, I laugh at all of you people who speak against twinking, running around East Commons in Bronze and swinging your little Runic Carver, trying to attack my twink and crying in tells after you're slaughtered. I am better suited for both PvP and PvE (not being stupid helps - most people are pathetic PvPers) and therefore happier for it. Yippie.<BR>
