	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hmmm from the looks of things, I'd say the only &quot;cry babies&quot; here are the people complaining about the &quot;cry baby&quot; higher levels.  Farming, on my server anyhow, is not THAT big a problem from what I've seen. example:  On an average day in LGuk just about every camp will have a GROUP in it, and vary rarly will you find a single &quot;high level&quot; character camping a rare spawn.  The way you people go on about it makes it sound like that EVERY SINGLE time you try and group ANYWHERE in the game there is always a &quot;Uber&quot; player camping where you want to camp.<BR>
<BR>
To be honest, farming is the quickest way to get money.  I don't intend to spend hours and hours in Karnors castle trying to get 1kpp just from the auto split.  &quot;So why don't you get some of the lewt that drops there?&quot; I her you cry!  Well, problem is once you get into the 50+ zones just about everything is done on a need before greed basis.  That means only people who CAN and WILL use an item can roll on it.  And if by chance an item that I CAN and WILL use drops, why the hell would I want to sell it?  It would be pointless selling an item that would be a welcome upgrade, unless you want to spend your EQ life with sub-par equip.  So as you see, most of the time your in a &quot;catch 22&quot; UNLESS an item goes &quot;gravy&quot; but then you have to roll against the group.  While I have NO PROBLEM with this (totaly fair idea IMO) my chances are only 1 in 6 for example.  BUT!  If I go to camp an item solo, guess who I have to roll against?  Yup you got it in one, nobody.  Item defaulted to me! =)<BR>
<BR>
And just a little FYI, farming is not without its risks.  For example my level 51 shaman was killed in crystal caverns when I was caught LoM in the stalag terror tunnel (some poor soul thought the terror tunnel was the way to the zone out, and he brought a whole army of spiders with him =)).  In Crystal Caverns, Everything except the named spawns are green, and even the named are low, low blue.  However just about everything still aggros me, and can really give me a pounding before I can turg, root, dot etc.  If the TLC was in use, maybe 4 or 5 mobs would actualy drop anything for me, while just about EVERYTHING would still be capable of killing me, if I had a turn of bad luck.  Trivial, does NOT mean having to use 50% or more mana on a mob that is capable of killing you given half a chance IMO, and this is why I glad to see the TLC will not be in use. =)<BR>
<BR>
Hope you enjoyed the read!<BR>
Menlaren Fizzlefoot 51st Gnome Cleric<BR>
&lt;Unseen University&gt;<BR>
Gazlaab Boghead 51st Troll Shaman<BR>
&lt;Not Guilded&gt;
				</font>
