				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Good Day All,<BR>
<BR>
First I'd like to address people who flame others for not using proper grammar when posting.  Now, last I checked it wasn't common pracice to consult the Hold Handbook when posting on Everlore.  I mean really, we're not turning in term papers here.  Give it a rest, there's no reason for it except that maybe you feel the need to pick on sombody here because you get picked on in real life.  People just freely speak their minds here, I personally didn't have ANY trouble reading S.Briarwood's Post.  As long as it's legible there's no problem.  And if you're saying that it wasn't legible, maybe that speaks of YOUR education level.<BR>
<BR>
Now, about the Trivial Loot Code.  The fact is that MOST people in the game don't farm the way everyone is complaining about.  What VI would be doing by implementing the TLC is taking away our freedom to play the game as it was designed and the majority, as proven by the many polls, prefers.  I am not a farmer, I don't agree with it, and I would hate it if I went somewhere where I can get experience and good loot but can't because there is a high level camping the spawns for the loot alone.  But what I DO like to do is explore areas I've never been to and still have the same chance to get the same loot when nobody else is there.  I am SO relieved that VI is not going to implement the TLC in SoL.  I was fearing having to create alts in several level ranges just so I could act out my curiosities.  I don't even think that the farming is as big an issue on every server, because in my 41 levels of living on my server, I've never had a problem with it.  I guess that's why I'm so against it.  I LOVE the game as it is.  I like going back to a zone and seeing that everything is green and that I can go get those Braided Ivy Cords from Thistle Underbrush because there is NOBODY ELSE THERE, and I don't have to go recuit sombody that's low evough level and trustworthy enough to loot them for me!  It's been said several times, it couldn't be more true, and I'm glad Verant agrees...you can't take away the freedoms of the majority based on the actions of a few.  Cheers Verant!<BR>
<BR>
Tryon
				</font>
